text.textblock: The above named national securities exchange has filed applications with the Securities and Exchange Commission (``Commission'') pursuant to Section 12(f)(1)(B) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 and Rule 12f-1 thereunder for unlisted trading privileges in the following securities:
Depositary Shares (rep. 1/100 sh. Cm. Cv. Exch. Pfd., $100.00 Par Value (File No. 7-12003).
Common Shares of Beneficial Interest, $.01 Par Value (File No. 7-12004).
Compania Boliviana de Energia Electrica, S.A.,
Common Stock, No Par Value (File No. 7-12005).
Ser. A Common Stock, $.01 Par Value (File No. 7-12008).
American Depositary Shares (rep. 1 Ord. sh., NGL 1.25 Par Value (File No. 7-12009).
$4.20 Cm. Exch. Ser. A Pfd. Stk. (File No. 7-12013).
New York State Gas & Electric Corp.,
Adj. Rte. Srl. Pfd., Ser. B Cum., $25.00 Par Value (File No. 7-12014).
Salomon Brothers Worldwide Income Fund, Inc.,
Common Vot. Stock, $.01 Par Value (File No. 7-12019).
These securities are listed and registered on one or more other national securities exchange and are reported in the consolidated transaction reporting system.

Interested persons are invited to submit on or before March 4, 1994, written data, views and arguments concerning the above-referenced applications. Persons desiring to make written comments should file three copies thereof with the Secretary of the Securities and Exchange Commission, 450 Fifth Street, NW., Washington, DC 20549. Following this opportunity for hearing, the Commission will approve the applications if it finds, based upon all the information available to it, that the extensions of unlisted trading privileges pursuant to such applications are consistent with the maintenance of fair and orderly markets and the protection of investors.
For the Commission, by the Division of Market Regulation, pursuant to delegated authority.
